		<div id="comment_body_64501589"><p>Banks only keep a fraction of the assets needed to pay back all their customers because not everyone requests the bank to pay them back at the same time.</p><p>Same thing here: not all the cars need charging at the same time.</p><p>And as we all know, this has never failed for the banking industry. So it's fine.</p></div>
