	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64501715">America is quite a ways behind Europe in EV infrastructure. I don't see that <a href="https://www.reuters.com/business/autos-transportation/inside-story-elon-musks-mass-firings-tesla-supercharger-staff-2024-05-15/" title="reuters.com">Musk firing Tesla's charging infrastructure team</a> [reuters.com] is going to improve that situation in the US.
<br> <br>
The US needs to start building compatible, interoperable EV infrastructure. All brands of EV charger must be able to charge all brands of EV. That's what Europe has done for a long time. It makes sense and it works.</div>
