		<div id="comment_body_64503557">BEV utes (pick ups) are now starting to appear.  Given time farmers will adopt them because they are not BEV hater, they are simply practical.  With plenty of space and solar panels becoming quite cheap the farmers will run the numbers, they are good at that, and when charging BEV farm vehicles from solar works out cheaper than trucking in gas they will switch over.  It is simply a mater of time.  I live rural I have notice that BEV cars are already becoming popular since all rural homes have electricity bu</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64503557">

</div>
